@Database DOOR_Speed_XX

@Index HBBS:Docs/Misc/Index.guide/MAIN

@Node Main "Speed_XX"

  Speed_XX
  ========

    Where XX is the baud rate that the user connected at

    This door does not exist, but Node calls this system door after an
    existing user has logged in to the system.

    This gives you the potention to write a door that asks users who
    connect at low baud rates for a password or you can just call a stats
    generator or what ever!

    I just thought it'd be usefull to implement the call to this
    system door.

@EndNode

